y, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Tewkesbury, Gloucestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Malmesbury, Wiltshire district, Wiltshire, England":"Malmesbury, Wiltshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1470–1505":"1470–1505","1474–1574":"1474–1574","1496–Male":"1496–Deceased","1498–Male":"1498–Deceased","1505–1553":"1505–1553","1444–1470":"1444–1470","1445–1505":"1445–1505","1445":"1445","1444":"1444","1498":"1498","1465":"1465","1553":"1553","Abt 1496":"about 1496","1574":"1574","1496":"1496","1474":"1474","1495":"1495","1470":"1470","1505":"1505","Buckland, Gloucestershire, England":"Buckland, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom","Tewkesbury, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Tewkesbury, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom","Malmesbury, Wiltshire district, Wiltshire, England":"Malmesbury, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hanks","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Hanke</i>, with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>. In England this personal name was a shortened form of both   Hankin   and   Hancock  , both of which were used as pet forms of   Henry  . The equivalent Middle Dutch names <i>Hanke</i> and <i>Hankin</i>, however, had the sense ‘young John’ and may have been introduced to England by Flemish settlers after the Conquest. There is no evidence to support the suggestion that an English hereditary surname was formed from the Old Norse personal name <i>Anki</i>, a diminutive of personal names such as <i>Arngrim</i> and <i>Arnketill</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Hankes","meanings":["English: variant of   Hanks  .","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): metronymic from the Yiddish female personal name <i>Khanke</i> (a pet form of <i>Khane</i>, from Hebrew <i>Ḥanna</i>; see   Hanna   6), with the Yiddish possessive suffix <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Hankin","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Yaron, Abbe, Isadore, Myer, Yitzhak.","English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Hankin</i>, a pet form of   Hann  , which in English usage was usually a short form of <i>Hanry</i> (Henry), and occasionally perhaps a rhyming pet form of <i>Randal</i> (Randolph). In Middle Dutch, <i>Hankin</i> was a pet form of <i>Johan</i> (John), a usage which may have been brought to England by Flemings after the Norman Conquest, but no examples have yet been found in Middle English where a man named <i>John</i> was also called <i>Hankin</i>. Compare   Henkin  ,   Hanks  , and   Hancock  .","English: from Middle English <i>Handekin</i>, a pet form of the personal name <i>Hand</i>, <i>Hond</i> (see   Hand  )."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John Hanks III was born in 1470, his father, John Hanks Jr, was 26 and his mother, Louise, was 25. He married Elizabeth Berger in 1495, in Buckland, Gloucestershire, England. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. He died in 1505, at the age of 35."},"et":{"1470–1505":"1470–1505","1474–1574":"1474–1574","1496–Male":"1496–Surnud","1498–Male":"1498–Surnud","1505–1553":"1505–1553","1444–1470":"1444–1470","1445–1505":"1445–1505","1445":"1445","1444":"1444","1498":"1498","1465":"1465","1553":"1553","Abt 1496":"umbes 1496","1574":"1574","1496":"1496","1474":"1474","1495":"1495","1470":"1470","1505":"1505","Buckland, Gloucestershire, England":"Buckland, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Tewkesbury, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Tewkesbury, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Malmesbury, Wiltshire district, Wiltshire, England":"Malmesbury, Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1470–1505":"1470–1505","1474–1574":"1474–1574","1496–Male":"1496–Kuollut","1498–Male":"1498–Kuollut","1505–1553":"1505–1553","1444–1470":"1444–1470","1445–1505":"1445–1505","14